label: A2B_cF192_216_2e2h_ab2eg-001
title: Low Temperature TmNi$_{2}$ Structure
comments:
TmNi$_{2}$ is found in three forms (Deutz, 1989): \begin{itemize} \item A \href{current_web_home_dir/A2B_cF192_216_2e2h_ab2eg-001}{low temperature face-centered cubic structure} (this structure) at room temperature and below, \item a \href{current_web_home_dir/A2B_cP24_215_ei_ace-001}{simple cubic structure} near 700$^\circ$, and \item the \href{current_web_home_dir/A2B_cF24_227_c_b-001}{$C15$ cubic Laves structure} for higher temperatures. \end{itemize} ~ \vspace{-.25in} 
  The data for this structure was taken at 4.2K.
